`Both approaches solve the problem within the given constraints.


**Approach 1 (3D DP)** is intuitive because it directly models the decision on each day, keeping track of the number of moves and the state (holding or not holding).
**Approach 2 (Optimized 1D DP)** exploits the alternating nature of operations. It reduces the space usage by maintaining only one array and updating it in reverse order.
Understanding these methods will help you make design decisions in similar problems and gain insights into different ways to optimize DP solutions.
